TOOL_USE: Write({"file_path": "/home/joe/Documents/repo/skill/sci-draw/.claude/_eval_sandbox_home/.claude/plans/valiant-shimmying-torvalds.md", "content": "# Lab Sensor Dashboard — Implementation Plan\n\n## Context\n\nThe user needs an **interactive dashboard** to monitor real-time sensor data from their lab. The dashboard should connect to a **PostgreSQL** database, use **Plotly/Dash** for visualization, and support filtering by **time range** and **device type**. This is a new feature built as a separate module within the existing sci-draw project.\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\nsci-draw/sensor_dashboard/\n├── __init__.py                # Package marker\n├── app.py                     # Dash app entry point, layout assembly\n├── config.py                  # Database config, app settings (env vars + defaults)\n├── database.py                # PostgreSQL connection pool, query functions\n├── callbacks.py               # All Dash callbacks (filtering, refresh, export)\n├── mock_data.py               # Generate & insert mock sensor data for dev/testing\n├── assets/\n│   └── style.css              # Dashboard styling\n├── sql/\n│   └── schema.sql             # CREATE TABLE statements + indexes\n├── .env.example               # Environment variable template\n└── requirements-dash.txt      # Dash-specific dependencies\n```\n\n### Tech Stack\n- **Dash** (with Plotly) — interactive web dashboard\n- **psycopg2** + connection pool — PostgreSQL access\n- **python-dotenv** — environment configuration\n- **pandas** — data wrangling for Plotly traces\n\n### Database Schema\n\nTwo tables:\n\n```sql\nsensor_devices (\n    device_id   SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n    device_name VARCHAR(128) NOT NULL,\n    device_type VARCHAR(64)  NOT NULL,  -- temperature, humidity, pressure, pH, etc.\n    location    VARCHAR(256),\n    unit        VARCHAR(32),            -- °C, %, hPa\n    created_at  TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()\n);\n\nsensor_readings (\n    reading_id   BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n    device_id    INT REFERENCES sensor_devices(device_id),\n    value        DOUBLE PRECISION NOT NULL,\n    recorded_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),\n    status       VARCHAR(32) DEFAULT 'normal'  -- 'normal', 'warning', 'alarm'\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_readings_device_time ON sensor_readings(device_id, recorded_at DESC);\n```\n\n### Dashboard Layout\n\n**Top bar**: Title + refresh controls (manual refresh button, auto-refresh toggle with interval selector 5s/10s/30s/60s)\n\n**Filter row**:\n- **Preset time buttons**: 1h, 6h, 24h, 7d, 30d, All\n- **Custom date range picker**: DatePickerRange (start/end)\n- **Device type dropdown**: Multi-select (temperature, humidity, pressure, etc.)\n- **Device name dropdown**: Multi-select, dynamically filtered by selected types\n\n**Main content area** — 2 rows × 3 columns grid:\n\n| Metric card: Current temp | Metric card: Current humidity | Metric card: Latest reading |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Main time-series chart** (full width, spans 2 cols) | **Device status table** (recent devices, 1 col) |\n\n**Bottom**: Export button (CSV download of filtered data)\n\n### Data Flow\n\n1. User adjusts filters → callbacks trigger re-query\n2. `database.py` runs parameterized SQL queries against PostgreSQL\n3. Results returned as pandas DataFrames\n4. Plotly traces rebuilt from filtered DataFrames\n5. Auto-refresh: `dcc.Interval` component triggers periodic re-query\n6. CSV export: callback streams filtered DataFrame as downloadable CSV\n\n### Mock Data Strategy\n\n`mock_data.py` generates realistic lab sensor data:\n- 5 device types × 2 locations = 10 devices\n- Readings at ~1 minute intervals over the past 7 days\n- Realistic noise/variation per sensor type (temperature: ±0.5°C, humidity: ±3%, etc.)\n- Occasional \"warning\" and \"alarm\" status readings\n\n## Concurrency & Connection Safety\n\n- **Connection pool** (`psycopg2.pool.ThreadedConnectionPool`): max 5 connections, shared across Dash callbacks\n- Pool opened on app start via `app.server.before_first_request`, closed on shutdown\n- Fallback: If PostgreSQL is unavailable, a `MockDB` class serves sample data from in-memory pandas DataFrames so the dashboard works standalone\n\n## Files to Create\n\n1. **`sci-draw/sensor_dashboard/sql/schema.sql`** — Database schema DDL\n2. **`sci-draw/sensor_dashboard/config.py`** — Load DB config from env vars, app-wide constants\n3. **`sci-draw/sensor_dashboard/database.py`** — Connection pool + query functions + MockDB fallback\n4. **`sci-draw/sensor_dashboard/mock_data.py`** — Generate realistic sensor data for dev/testing\n5. **`sci-draw/sensor_dashboard/callbacks.py`** — All Dash callbacks\n6. **`sci-draw/sensor_dashboard/app.py`** — Main Dash app, layout assembly, entry point\n7. **`sci-draw/sensor_dashboard/assets/style.css`** — Styling\n8. **`sci-draw/sensor_dashboard/.env.example`** — Template for DB credentials\n9. **`sci-draw/sensor_dashboard/requirements-dash.txt`** — Dependencies\n\n## Verification\n\n1. **Dev mode**: Run `python -m sci-draw.sensor_dashboard.app` with no PostgreSQL → dashboard starts using MockDB fallback with pre-generated data\n2. **With PostgreSQL**: Set `PGHOST`, `PGDATABASE` etc. in `.env`, create tables with `schema.sql`, run `mock_data.py` to populate, then start app\n3. **Test filters**: Change time presets → chart updates; toggle device types → traces appear/disappear; use date picker → data window changes\n4. **Test auto-refresh**: Enable auto-refresh → new data appears (mock mode simulates advancing timestamps)\n5. **Test CSV export**: Click export button → CSV file downloads with filtered data\n"})
